<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1650,1927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,354,1686,1711]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Distribution.</emphasis>
Western Atlantic—North Carolina to 
<collectingCountry box="[838,907,1686,1710]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(Amapá to Rio Grande do Sul). Eastern Atlantic—Cape Verde, 
<collectingCountry box="[412,501,1722,1746]" name="Senegal" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Senegal</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[537,621,1722,1746]" name="Nigeria" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Crosnier" box="[636,906,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Crosnier, A. &amp; Forest, J. (1966) Crustaces Decapodes: Alpheidae. In: Campagne de La Calypso dans de Golfe de Guinee et aux Iles Principe, Sao Tome et Annobon (1956), et campagne aus Iles du Cap Vert (1959) (suite). Parte 19, Resultats Scientifiques des Campagnes de la Calypso, 7 (27). Annales de l'Institute Oceanographique, Monaco, 44, 199 - 314." type="journal article" year="1966">
Crosnier &amp; Forest 
<number box="[847,906,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Christoffersen" box="[917,1143,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Christoffersen, M. L. (1998) Malacostraca. Eucarida. Caridea. Crangonoidea and Alpheoidea (Except Glyphocrangonidae and Crangonidae). In: Young, P. S. (Ed), Catalogue of Crustacea of Brazil. Museu Nacional, Rio de Janeiro, p. 351 - 372." type="book chapter" year="1998">
Christoffersen 
<number box="[1084,1143,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Coelho 
<emphasis box="[1243,1299,1723,1747]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1305,1366,1722,1746]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="2006.0">2006</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1650,1927]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,405,1758,1783]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Ecological notes.</emphasis>
The single specimen from 
<taxonomicName box="[734,799,1758,1782]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Lysmata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bahia">Bahia</taxonomicName>
was collected from a burrow of unidentified host (or perhaps its own burrow, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Dworschak" box="[471,783,1794,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Dworschak, P. C. &amp; Coelho, V. R. (1999) On two alpheids from Araca (Sao Paulo, Brazil) with a description of a new species of Leptalpheus (Decapoda: Caridea: Alpheidae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museum in Wien, 101 B, 475 - 488." type="journal article" year="1999">
Dworschak &amp; Coelho 
<number box="[723,783,1794,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), in fine sand in the intertidal zone, at a salinity of 
<number box="[1355,1383,1794,1818]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="35.0">35</number>
psu. Although primarily a shallow-water species (less than 
<quantity box="[763,823,1830,1854]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="50.0">50 m</quantity>
), 
<taxonomicName box="[844,993,1830,1854]" class="Malacostraca" family="Alpheidae" genus="Automate" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evermanni">
<emphasis box="[844,993,1830,1854]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">A. evermanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from as deep as 
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="m" value="250.0">250 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[187,350,1866,1890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1901) The Brachyura and Macrura of Porto Rico. Bulletin of the United States Fish Commission, 20 (2), 1 - 127." type="journal article" year="1901">
Rathbun 
<number box="[291,350,1866,1890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1901.0">1901</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Crosnier" box="[361,630,1866,1890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Crosnier, A. &amp; Forest, J. (1966) Crustaces Decapodes: Alpheidae. In: Campagne de La Calypso dans de Golfe de Guinee et aux Iles Principe, Sao Tome et Annobon (1956), et campagne aus Iles du Cap Vert (1959) (suite). Parte 19, Resultats Scientifiques des Campagnes de la Calypso, 7 (27). Annales de l'Institute Oceanographique, Monaco, 44, 199 - 314." type="journal article" year="1966">
Crosnier &amp; Forest 
<number box="[571,630,1866,1890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1966.0">1966</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dworschak" box="[641,952,1866,1890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refString="Dworschak, P. C. &amp; Coelho, V. R. (1999) On two alpheids from Araca (Sao Paulo, Brazil) with a description of a new species of Leptalpheus (Decapoda: Caridea: Alpheidae). Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museum in Wien, 101 B, 475 - 488." type="journal article" year="1999">
Dworschak &amp; Coelho 
<number box="[892,952,1866,1890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1999.0">1999</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
